oi-build-firmware (0.6.6.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Trying to unmount /var/cache/apt/archives in /rootfs-* before removing
    it. Recent change in slind-control introduced mount-binding
    directories, so plain rm -rf won't work anymore.

 -- Mikhail Gusarov <dottedmag@dottedmag.net>  Fri, 29 Aug 2008 05:21:47 +0700

oi-build-firmware (0.6.6) unstable; urgency=low

  * "Dehackization" release.

  * No longer touch dropbear initscript - now it works well enough.
  * S03kexec-reload functionality was integrated to boot-local-kernel
    package - install it instead of writing initscript manually.
  * Stop creating /vmlinuz symlink - it is handled by linux-image package.

 -- Mikhail Gusarov <dottedmag@dottedmag.net>  Sun, 24 Aug 2008 18:09:27 +0700

